#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:145
msgid "Death of Deoran, Minister Hylas, or Ethiliel"
msgstr "Muerte de Deoran, del ministro Hylas o Ethiliel"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:162
msgid "I have failed my kingdom and duty..."
msgstr "He fallado a mi reino y a mi deber..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:179
msgid ""
"They’ve broken through the trapdoor and entered the refugee cellar! Even if "
"we could still manage to win by force of arms, Westin is doomed without its "
"people..."
msgstr ""
"¡Han roto la trampilla y entrado en el sótano de los refugiados! Incluso si "
"aún pudiéramos ganar por la fuerza, Westin está condenado sin su gente..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:207
msgid "Taste cold steel!"
msgstr "¡Prueba el frío acero!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:223
msgid "Yeah... I should’ve figured I wouldn’t get a happy ending..."
msgstr "Sí... ya debía imaginar que no tendría un final feliz..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:242
msgid "I have given all in service of my kingdom..."
msgstr "He dado todo al servicio de mi reino..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:262
msgid "May the Light guide you where I have failed..."
msgstr "Que la Luz te guíe donde yo he fallado..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_characters.cfg:282
msgid ""
"I have lost everything helping the humans... Now they will surely perish!"
msgstr ""
"He perdido todo ayudando a los humanos... ¡Ahora seguramente perecerán!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:75
msgid ""
"One of your units has reached max XP, and has advanced a level! It is now "
"significantly more powerful, and has been fully healed!\n"
"\n"
"For a full description of what one of your units can do, <b><i>right-click "
"it and select “Unit Type Description.”</i></b>"
msgstr ""
"¡Una de tus unidades ha alcanzado la XP máxima y subido de nivel! Ahora es "
"significativamente más poderosa y ha sido completamente curada.\n"
"\n"
"Para una descripción completa de lo que puede hacer una de tus unidades, "
"<b><i>haz clic derecho sobre ella y selecciona “Descripción del tipo de "
"unidad”.</i></b>"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:94
msgid ""
"\n"
"Most scenarios have a turn limit, as\n"
"shown in the upper-left-hand corner.\n"
"Usually, running out of turns will\n"
"result in defeat — check your\n"
"<i><b>objectives</b></i> by clicking the <i><b>“Menu”</b></i>\n"
"button in the top-left corner \n"
"(or use the hotkey <i><b>Ctrl+J</b></i>).\n"
"\n"
"Finishing early will usually reward \n"
"a gold boost (“early finish bonus”) \n"
"in the next scenario, so don’t delay!"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"La mayoría de los escenarios tienen un límite de turnos, como\n"
"se muestra en la esquina superior izquierda.\n"
"Usualmente, quedarse sin turnos\n"
"resultará en derrota — revisa tus\n"
"<i><b>objetivos</b></i> haciendo clic en el <i><b>“Menú”</b></i>\n"
"en la esquina superior izquierda \n"
"(o usa la tecla rápida <i><b>Ctrl+J</b></i>).\n"
"\n"
"Terminar antes generalmente recompensa \n"
"con un bono de oro (“bono por finalización temprana”) \n"
"en el siguiente escenario, ¡así que no tardes!"

#. [message]: id=Ethiliel,Hylas {NOT race=mechanical}
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:129
msgid ""
"My healing magic is potent, but I cannot use it to heal myself. I’ll have to "
"spend some time in a village to recover."
msgstr ""
"Mi magia curativa es potente, pero no puedo usarla para curarme. Tendré que "
"pasar un tiempo en un pueblo para recuperarme."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:151
msgid ""
"I just made a <i><b>ranged attack</b></i>! I had to stand right next to this "
"Quintain <i>(yes, this is different from how most games handle ranged "
"attacks)</i>, but because the dummy has no ranged weapon of its own it was "
"unable to retaliate."
msgstr ""
"¡Acabo de realizar un <i><b>ataque a distancia</b></i>! Tuve que estar justo "
"al lado de esta Quintana <i>(sí, esto es diferente de cómo la mayoría de los "
"juegos manejan los ataques a distancia)</i>, pero como el muñeco no tiene "
"arma a distancia propia, no pudo contraatacar."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. second_unit may be a Walking Corpse, Ghoul, Skeleton, or one of their advancements
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:159
msgid ""
"I just made a <i><b>ranged attack</b></i>! I had to stand right next to this "
"$second_unit.language_name <i>(yes, this is different from how most games "
"handle ranged attacks)</i>, but because the $second_unit.language_name has "
"no ranged weapon of its own it was unable to retaliate."
msgstr ""
"¡Acabo de realizar un <i><b>ataque a distancia</b></i>! Tuve que estar justo "
"al lado de este $second_unit.language_name <i>(sí, esto es diferente de cómo "
"la mayoría de los juegos manejan los ataques a distancia)</i>, pero como "
"$second_unit.language_name no tiene arma a distancia propia, no pudo "
"contraatacar."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. second_unit may be a Thug (always male) or one of its advancements
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:167
msgid ""
"I just made a <i><b>ranged attack</b></i>! I had to stand right next to this "
"$second_unit.language_name <i>(yes, this is different from how most games "
"handle ranged attacks)</i>, but because the $second_unit.language_name has "
"no ranged weapon of his own he was unable to retaliate."
msgstr ""
"¡Acabo de realizar un <i><b>ataque a distancia</b></i>! Tuve que estar justo "
"al lado de este $second_unit.language_name <i>(sí, esto es diferente de cómo "
"la mayoría de los juegos manejan los ataques a distancia)</i>, pero como "
"$second_unit.language_name no tiene arma a distancia propia, no pudo "
"contraatacar."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:191
msgid ""
"Our bows and spears are nearly useless against these skeletons! They have "
"nothing for our shafts to pierce but air!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nuestros arcos y lanzas son casi inútiles contra estos esqueletos! ¡No hay "
"nada que nuestros proyectiles puedan atravesar salvo aire!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:195
msgid ""
"To see what damage resistances and vulnerabilities a unit has, right-click "
"it and select “Unit Type Description.”"
msgstr ""
"Para ver qué resistencias y vulnerabilidades tiene una unidad, haz clic "
"derecho sobre ella y selecciona “Descripción del tipo de unidad.”"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:219
msgid ""
"I perish! Such wasted potential! I’d gained much experience, and was close "
"to becoming something more..."
msgstr ""
"¡Perezco! ¡Qué potencial desperdiciado! Había ganado mucha experiencia, y "
"estaba cerca de convertirme en algo más..."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:225
msgid ""
"One of your high-experience units has died! Take care to protect your "
"experienced soldiers, so that they can eventually advance to powerful Level "
"2 veterans."
msgstr ""
"¡Una de tus unidades de alta experiencia ha muerto! Cuida de proteger a tus "
"soldados experimentados, para que eventualmente avancen a poderosos "
"veteranos de nivel 2."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:246
msgid ""
"Argh, I fall! All my hard-won battle experience is lost! I will not be easy "
"to replace, Deoran..."
msgstr ""
"¡Argh, caigo! ¡Toda mi experiencia de batalla duramente ganada se pierde! No "
"seré fácil de reemplazar, Deoran..."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:252
msgid ""
"One of your high-level veterans has died! Take care to protect your promoted "
"soldiers, so that you can recall them in future battles."
msgstr ""
"¡Uno de tus veteranos de alto nivel ha muerto! Cuida de proteger a tus "
"soldados promovidos, para que puedas recordarlos en batallas futuras."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. $consecutive_misses will be 3 or higher. Alternatively, can be translated along the lines of "I missed all my strikes!"
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:308
msgid ""
"I missed all $consecutive_misses strikes! I tried my best, but this enemy "
"had a high chance to dodge. I might have had better odds attacking a "
"different enemy."
msgstr ""
"¡Fallé todos mis $consecutive_misses golpes! Hice lo mejor que pude, pero "
"este enemigo tenía una alta probabilidad de esquivar. Tal vez hubiera tenido "
"mejores probabilidades atacando a un enemigo diferente."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:312
msgid ""
"A good commander understands the odds, and knows how to both exploit good "
"luck and mitigate bad luck. After all, both good and bad luck are equally "
"likely!"
msgstr ""
"Un buen comandante entiende las probabilidades y sabe cómo aprovechar la "
"buena suerte y mitigar la mala suerte. ¡Después de todo, tanto la buena como "
"la mala suerte son igualmente probables!"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:315
msgid "Managing Luck"
msgstr "Gestionando la suerte"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:317
msgid ""
"Wesnoth is a game about flexible strategy,\n"
"not deterministic calculation.\n"
"Anyone can win when things go as planned.\n"
"Wesnoth’s skill & mastery lie in creating\n"
"a strategy that <i><b>mitigates bad luck</b></i>, while\n"
"simultaneously <i><b>exploits good luck</b></i>. Both\n"
"bad and good luck are inevitable, so be \n"
"ready to handle both!\n"
"\n"
"Expert players are so skilled at this that\n"
"they can prevail in every campaign on even \n"
"the highest difficulty, without save-loading!\n"
"\n"
"That said, if you really prefer a more\n"
"deterministic experience, try selecting\n"
"<i><b>“Reduced RNG”</b></i> when starting a new \n"
"campaign."
msgstr ""
"Wesnoth es un juego sobre estrategia flexible,\n"
"no cálculo determinista.\n"
"Cualquiera puede ganar cuando todo sale según lo planeado.\n"
"La habilidad y maestría en Wesnoth radica en crear\n"
"una estrategia que <i><b>mitigue la mala suerte</b></i>, mientras\n"
"simultáneamente <i><b>aprovecha la buena suerte</b></i>. Tanto la mala como "
"la buena suerte son inevitables, así que prepárate para manejar ambas!\n"
"\n"
"Los jugadores expertos son tan hábiles que\n"
"pueden triunfar en todas las campañas incluso\n"
"en la dificultad más alta, ¡sin cargar partidas guardadas!\n"
"\n"
"Dicho esto, si realmente prefieres una experiencia más\n"
"determinista, prueba seleccionando\n"
"<i><b>“RNG reducido”</b></i> al iniciar una nueva\n"
"campaña."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. $consecutive_hits will be 3 or higher. Alternatively, can be translated along the lines of "I got lucky and hit all my strikes!"
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:357
msgid ""
"I got lucky and hit all $consecutive_hits strikes! Good luck will sometimes "
"happen, but a good commander knows how to win without relying on it. After "
"all, bad luck happens just as often as good luck!"
msgstr ""
"Tuve suerte y acerté todos mis $consecutive_hits ataques! A veces ocurre la "
"buena suerte, pero un buen comandante sabe cómo ganar sin depender de ella. "
"¡Después de todo, la mala suerte ocurre con la misma frecuencia que la buena!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:380
msgid ""
"I missed all $consecutive_misses strikes, even though my enemy had a low "
"chance to dodge! That’s unlucky, but bad luck happens just as often as good "
"luck — a good commander knows how to plan around both!"
msgstr ""
"¡Fallé todos mis $consecutive_misses ataques, a pesar de que mi enemigo "
"tenía baja probabilidad de esquivar! Eso es mala suerte, pero la mala suerte "
"ocurre con la misma frecuencia que la buena — un buen comandante sabe cómo "
"planear en torno a ambas."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:403
msgid ""
"I hit all $consecutive_hits strikes, even though my enemy had a high chance "
"to dodge! Luck works both ways — sometimes I miss strikes when I was likely "
"to hit, but sometimes I also hit strikes that I was likely to miss — like "
"now!"
msgstr ""
"Acerté todos mis $consecutive_hits ataques, aunque mi enemigo tenía alta "
"probabilidad de esquivar. La suerte funciona en ambos sentidos — a veces "
"fallo ataques que probablemente acertaría, pero otras veces acierto ataques "
"que probablemente fallaría — ¡como ahora!"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:413
msgid "Allies"
msgstr "Aliados"

#. [display_tip]
#. while this message is partly to explain about allies, it's mostly to 1) remind the player about Alt+S and 2) explain how Peasants and Woodsmen work (since the player may control them soon)
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:416
msgid ""
"Allies can range from basic, immobile guards to full-fledged\n"
"factions with their own income, leaders, and AI. To see how\n"
"much gold and income each side has, press <b><i>Alt+S</i></b>.\n"
"\n"
"In this scenario, your allies include Peasants and Woodsmen. \n"
"Like Walking Corpses, <b><i>Peasants and Woodsmen are level 0 and\n"
"thus do not exert a Zone of Control</i></b>. Enemies can move\n"
"around them unhindered."
msgstr ""
"Los aliados pueden ir desde simples guardias inmóviles hasta facciones "
"completas\n"
"con sus propios ingresos, líderes e IA. Para ver cuánto oro e ingresos tiene "
"cada bando,\n"
"presiona <b><i>Alt+S</i></b>.\n"
"\n"
"En este escenario, tus aliados incluyen Campesinos y Leñadores.\n"
"Al igual que los Cadáveres Andantes, <b><i>los Campesinos y Leñadores son de "
"nivel 0 y\n"
"por lo tanto no ejercen Zona de Control</i></b>. Los enemigos pueden "
"moverse\n"
"a su alrededor sin impedimentos."

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:433
msgid "Accelerated Speed"
msgstr "Velocidad acelerada"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:435
msgid ""
"If movement and combat are taking too long,\n"
"you can enable <i><b>Accelerated Speed</b></i> and/or \n"
"<i><b>Skip AI Moves</b></i> in the Preferences menu."
msgstr ""
"Si el movimiento y el combate tardan demasiado,\n"
"puedes activar <i><b>Velocidad acelerada</b></i> y/o \n"
"<i><b>Saltar movimientos de IA</b></i> en el menú de Preferencias."

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:447
msgid "Building a Powerful Army"
msgstr "Construyendo un ejército poderoso"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:449
msgid ""
"Units gain experience with each attack, and much more with each kill.\n"
"<i><b>Most campaigns expect</b></i> you to recall the same veterans across "
"each battle,\n"
"building experience and eventually accumulating <i><b>a roster of powerful "
"level-2\n"
"or level-3 units.</b></i>\n"
"\n"
"If you don’t have many level-2 or level-3 units right now, don’t despair!\n"
"This campaign is not excessively difficult and can still be completed\n"
"with a weak army, though it may require skilled tactics. But in future\n"
"campaigns, <i><b>be sure to protect your veterans and build them into a "
"powerful\n"
"army.</b></i>"
msgstr ""
"Las unidades ganan experiencia con cada ataque, y mucho más con cada "
"muerte.\n"
"<i><b>La mayoría de las campañas esperan</b></i> que reutilices a los mismos "
"veteranos en cada batalla,\n"
"acumulando experiencia y eventualmente reuniendo <i><b>una lista de "
"poderosas\n"
"unidades de nivel 2 o nivel 3.</b></i>\n"
"\n"
"Si no tienes muchas unidades de nivel 2 o nivel 3 ahora, ¡no desesperes!\n"
"Esta campaña no es excesivamente difícil y aún puede completarse\n"
"con un ejército débil, aunque podría requerir tácticas hábiles. Pero en "
"futuras\n"
"campañas, <i><b>asegúrate de proteger a tus veteranos y convertirlos en un\n"
"ejército poderoso.</b></i>"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:461
msgid "Sacrificial Lambs"
msgstr "Corderos sacrificables"

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:463
msgid "On the topic of protecting veterans..."
msgstr "Sobre el tema de proteger a los veteranos..."

#. [display_tip]
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_help.cfg:465
msgid ""
"In challenging scenarios, it's often\n"
"impossible to protect every unit.\n"
"\n"
"Instead of sending your veterans \n"
"straight into the meatgrinder, it's\n"
"often best to use them alongside\n"
"fresh recruits or disposable units.\n"
"\n"
"Doing so can help spare your\n"
"veterans from the worst of the \n"
"enemy's attacks."
msgstr ""
"En escenarios desafiantes, a menudo\n"
"es imposible proteger a todas las unidades.\n"
"\n"
"En lugar de enviar a tus veteranos \n"
"directamente al matadero, a menudo\n"
"es mejor usarlos junto con\n"
"reclutas novatos o unidades prescindibles.\n"
"\n"
"Hacer esto puede ayudar a proteger a tus\n"
"veteranos de los peores ataques del\n"
"enemigo."

#. [part]
#. Intro to scenario 4
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_story.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Ethiliel led the South Guard through the southern forest. The deep woods "
"became overcast with unnatural shadow as they traveled, shrouded with eerie "
"silence and uncanny stillness. Grey darkness sapped all color from their "
"murky surroundings, with every movement and sound muted in the thick fog. "
"Their small company kept vigilant watch on the dense forest and on each "
"other, wary of the foreboding ambience.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, Ethiliel told them to halt and pitch camp — they had reached the "
"Black River, beyond which no elf or man would willingly pass."
msgstr ""
"Ethiliel condujo a la Guardia del Sur a través del bosque meridional. Los "
"profundos bosques se cubrieron de una sombra antinatural mientras avanzaban, "
"envueltos en un silencio inquietante y una quietud sobrecogedora. Una "
"oscuridad gris drenaba todo color de su turbio entorno, con cada movimiento "
"y sonido amortiguados por la densa niebla. Su pequeña compañía mantenía una "
"vigilancia constante sobre el espeso bosque y entre ellos mismos, recelosa "
"del ambiente amenazador.\n"
"\n"
"Finalmente, Ethiliel les indicó que se detuvieran y levantaran campamento: "
"habían llegado al Río Negro, más allá del cual ningún elfo ni humano pasaría "
"de buen grado."

#. [part]
#. Intro to scenario 5
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_story.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Guided by Urza Afalas, Deoran and his company marched northwards, back "
"across the Black River.\n"
"\n"
"The ominous gloom of the forest seemed to lift behind them as the tired "
"soldiers returned towards the land of men. But even as the dark magic faded "
"into memory, a new threat made itself known in the form of subtle footfalls "
"amongst the trees..."
msgstr ""
"Guiados por Urza Afalas, Deoran y su compañía marcharon hacia el norte, de "
"regreso a través del Río Negro.\n"
"\n"
"La ominosa penumbra del bosque parecía disiparse tras ellos mientras los "
"soldados cansados regresaban a la tierra de los hombres. Pero incluso cuando "
"la magia oscura se desvanecía en la memoria, una nueva amenaza se hacía "
"presente en forma de sutiles pasos entre los árboles..."

#. [part]
#. Intro to scenario 5
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_story.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Absent Urza Afalas, Deoran and his company marched northwards, back across "
"the Black River.\n"
"\n"
"The ominous gloom of the forest seemed to lift behind them as the tired "
"soldiers returned towards the land of men. But even as the dark magic faded "
"into memory, a new threat made itself known in the form of subtle footfalls "
"amongst the trees..."
msgstr ""
"Sin Urza Afalas, Deoran y su compañía marcharon hacia el norte, de regreso a "
"través del Río Negro.\n"
"\n"
"La ominosa penumbra del bosque parecía disiparse tras ellos mientras los "
"soldados cansados regresaban a la tierra de los hombres. Pero incluso cuando "
"la magia oscura se desvanecía en la memoria, una nueva amenaza se hacía "
"presente en forma de sutiles pasos entre los árboles..."

#. [part]
#. Intro to scenario 5b
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/utils/sg_story.cfg:48
msgid ""
"Harried by an increasingly worried Ethiliel, Deoran and his company marched "
"quickly northwards out of the great southern forest.\n"
"\n"
"Yet even as they returned towards the land of men, the ominous gloom of the "
"forest followed them. Up above, the bright sun was shrouded with grey fog, "
"overcast with billowing clouds streaking through the sky in streams of "
"darkened ash. Behind, the crepuscular shadow spread outward from the forest, "
"an unnatural extension of the still-undefeated powers that lay within. It "
"gained quickly upon them, the sinister darkness creeping ever-faster toward "
"the men of the South Guard."
msgstr ""
"Presionados por un Ethiliel cada vez más preocupado, Deoran y su compañía "
"marcharon rápidamente hacia el norte, saliendo del gran bosque sureño.\n"
"\n"
"Pero incluso al regresar a la tierra de los hombres, la ominosa penumbra del "
"bosque los seguía. En lo alto, el sol brillante estaba cubierto por niebla "
"gris, sobrecargado de nubes ondulantes que atravesaban el cielo en "
"corrientes de ceniza oscura. Por detrás, la sombra crepuscular se expandía "
"desde el bosque, una extensión antinatural de los poderes aún no derrotados "
"que residían en su interior. Avanzaba rápidamente hacia ellos, la siniestra "
"oscuridad deslizándose cada vez más rápido hacia los hombres de la guardia "
"del sur."

